ruby-zoom
------------------------------------------
Ruby/ZOOM provides a Ruby binding to the Z39.50 Object-Orientation Model
(ZOOM), an abstract object-oriented programming interface to a subset of
the services specified by the Z39.50 standard, also known as the
international standard ISO 23950.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  libyaz3-3.0.6-1
  ruby-1.8.6-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.3.5-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  make-3.81-1
  ruby-1.8.6-1

Canonical website:
  http://ruby-zoom.rubyforge.org/

Canonical download:
  http://rubyforge.org/frs/?group_id=592

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack ruby-zoom-0.3.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./ruby-zoom-0.3.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ruby-zoom-0.3.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/ruby-zoom-0.3.0-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

